Looking at the filenames and example matches, I can see that the pattern extracts everything before `_quant.sf`.

The examples show:
- `HS01_1_quant.sf` → extract `HS01_1`
- `HS01_10_quant.sf` → extract `HS01_10`
- `HS01_11_quant.sf` → extract `HS01_11`

This pattern applies to all filenames - they all end with `_quant.sf` and we need to capture everything before that suffix.

3. Include special characters like spaces and parentheses (e.g., "ipNF05.5 (mixed clone)")

```json
{
  "regex": "(.+)_quant\\.sf"
}
```

This regex:
- `(.+)` - Captures one or more of any character (greedy matching)
- `_quant\\.sf` - Matches the literal string "_quant.sf" (with escaped dot)

The greedy `.+` will match as much as possible while still allowing the rest of the pattern to match, effectively capturing everything up to (but not including) `_quant.sf`.
